      • getTagsFromDocument

        public static java.util.List<java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>> getTagsFromDocument(java.lang.String documentURL)
        Given an input document specified by documentURL. Splits the document into sentences after which each sentence is split into word tokens. These words are then tagged with their POS tags after which only the POS tags are returned as a word list separated into sentences.
        Parameters:
        documentURL - The document URL for the text document to be read
        Returns:
        A double list split into sentences and words containing POS tags generated from the sentences in the document.

      • getTokenizedString

        public static java.util.List<java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>> getTokenizedString(java.lang.String documentURL)
        This one is similar to getTagsFromDocument(String) but instead of returning only the POS tags, it only returns the words. It's effectively a sentence and word tokenizer.
        Parameters:
        documentURL - The document to be tokenized
        Returns:
        The document found in documentURL tokenized into sentences and words.
        See Also:
        getTagsFromDocument(String)
